            { "text": "Finding zeroes of quadratic polynomials geometrically", "marks": "2", "important": true, "type": "concept" },
            { "text": "Cubic polynomial: sum of zeroes, sum of product of pairs, product of zeroes", "marks": "3", "important": false, "type": "formula" }
          ],
          "notes": {
            "content": [
              { "type": "intro", "text": "A polynomial p(x) = aₙxⁿ + … + a₀. The degree is the highest power." },
              { "type": "heading", "text": "Zeroes and Coefficients" },
              { "type": "text", "text": "For ax² + bx + c with zeroes α and β:" },
              { "type": "formula", "text": "α + β = –b/a    |    α·β = c/a" },
              { "type": "keypoint", "text": "Geometrically: zeroes = x-intercepts of the parabola y = ax² + bx + c" },
              { "type": "example", "question": "If α, β are zeroes of 2x² – 7x + 3, find α + β and α·β.", "answer": "α + β = 7/2,  α·β = 3/2" }
            ]
          },
          "quiz": [
            { "q": "For ax² + bx + c, sum of zeroes =", "options": ["c/a", "–b/a", "b/a", "–c/a"], "answer": 1 },
            { "q": "Max zeroes of a cubic polynomial:", "options": ["1", "2", "3", "4"], "answer": 2 },
            { "q": "Product of zeroes of 2x² – 8x + 6:", "options": ["4", "3", "–4", "–3"], "answer": 1 },
            { "q": "Degree of polynomial 3x³ – 2x² + x – 5:", "options": ["1", "2", "3", "5"], "answer": 2 }
          ],
